summary: I’m not saying that the Good Omens folks are doing a bad job with the marketing but.... It kinda bothers me to see this slew of...
body:
I’m not saying that the Good Omens folks are doing a bad job with the marketing but….

It kinda bothers me to see this slew of articles about how the marketing is incredible and everything is changing based on one event, in Texas of all places, that was inaccessible to most of the biggest fans while we spent months literally begging for content and being smack down when a clip leaked and we all watched it cause we were desperate for something new.

That said, the show creators and actors are amazing with the fandom and it is so refreshing after the horrible shit the general cast and creators of Sherlock said and did to fandom.

Also, hey amazing marketing team! Where is my Good Omens merch. I’m all about books but don’t pull a Sherlock and not release anything until much too late.

title: [Podfic] On the Wings of War
body:
read it on the AO3 at https://ift.tt/2FA8XvU

by Liannabob

(Originally posted on Amplificathon in 2012)

Summary (by Author):

The four Horsemen are not just people with fancy rings. They aren’t even demons with fancy rings. They are another species entirely, a force unto themselves, and Lucifer is kidding himself if he thinks that they are at his beck and call. They are separate. They are neutral. Dean Winchester is not built like them.

Spoilers up to 5.14, at which point events diverge…dramatically.
